HEADWORD: G-spot
<hw>G-spot</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from <person>Ernst
<ets>G</ets>r⟦aum⟧fenberg</person>, the gynecologist who first described
it.]</ety> <def>A small spot on the front wall of the vagina in women,
